[SN]TITLE[SN]
Arrest after child hit by quad bike in Pontypridd

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A male has been arrested after a child was involved in a collision with a quad bike in Rhondda Cynon Taff.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
South Wales Police said the incident happened on Margaret Street in Pontypridd at about 18:10 BST on Tuesday.
The child, who was a pedestrian, has been airlifted to hospital but the injuries are unknown.
Police said the male was riding the quad bike and is in police custody.
